<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,802,567,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1936" box="[240,451,567,590]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis box="[240,451,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Werner in 1936 from 
<collectingCountry box="[315,456,598,621]" name="Mozambique" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
and has been accepted as valid by other authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Vachon" box="[395,614,628,651]" firstAuthor="Vachon" page="179" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="170 - 184" refId="ref18287" refString="VACHON, M. 1940. Voyage en A. O. F. de L. Berland et J. Millot. Scorpions. V. Bull. Soc. Zool. France 65: 170 - 184." type="journal article" year="1940">Vachon, 1940: 179</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weidner" firstAuthor="Weidner" page="98" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="89 - 142" refId="ref18490" refString="WEIDNER, H. 1959. Die Entomologischen Sammlungen des Zoologischen Staatsinstituts und Zoologischen Museums Hamburg, I. Teil, Pararthropoda und Chelicerata I. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 57: 89 - 142." type="journal article" year="1959">Weidner, 1959: 98</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="LAMORAL, B. H. &amp; S. REYNDERS" box="[240,616,659,682]" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="489 - 576" part="22" refId="ref17245" refString="LAMORAL, B. H. &amp; S. REYNDERS 1975. A catalogue of the scorpions described from the Ethiopian Faunal Region up to December 1973. Annals of the Natal Museum, 22: 489 - 576." title="A catalogue of the scorpions described from the Ethiopian Faunal Region up to December 1973" type="journal article" year="1975">Lamoral &amp; Reynders, 1975: 498</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="KOVARIK, F." bookContentInfo="176 pp" journalOrPublisher="Jihlava (Czech Republic): Publishing House &quot; Madagaskar" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" refId="ref16585" refString="KOVARIK, F. 1998. Stiri [Scorpiones]. Jihlava (Czech Republic): Publishing House &quot; Madagaskar &quot;, 176 pp (in Czech)." title="Stiri [Scorpiones]" type="book" year="1998">Kovařík, 1998: 104</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="LOWE" box="[250,504,690,713]" firstAuthor="Fet" page="79" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref17483" refString="LOWE, G. 2000. A new species of Babycurus (Scorpiones: Buthidae) from northern Oman. Entomological News, 111: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="2000">Fet &amp; Lowe, 2000: 79</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="KOVARIK, F." box="[519,738,690,713]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="235 - 265" part="64" refId="ref16615" refString="KOVARIK, F. 2000. Revision of Babycurus with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 64: 235 - 265." title="Revision of Babycurus with descriptions of three new species (Scorpiones: Buthidae)" type="journal article" year="2000">Kovařík, 2000: 252</bibRefCitation>
). The first author (F.K.) recently studied the 
<typeStatus box="[624,680,720,743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 40– 49</figureCitation>
) and found that legs III and IV both bear tibial spurs (
<figureCitation box="[200,333,782,805]" captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
). This character is diagnostic for the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="C. L. Koch, 1845" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1845" box="[192,470,812,835]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Lychas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,267,812,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Lychas</emphasis>
C. L. Koch, 1845
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1886" box="[688,802,812,835]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[688,802,812,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Šťáhlavský, 2018" authorityName="Kovařík &amp; Lowe &amp; Šťáhlavský" authorityYear="2018" box="[238,388,843,866]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Barbaracurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[238,388,843,866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Barbaracurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[395,470,842,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[395,435,842,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">gen</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[449,464,842,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, leg III lacks tibial spurs (only present on leg IV) (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[454,599,874,897]" captionStart="Figures 95–106" captionStartId="14.[192,278,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[191,1440,191,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-16@14.[192,1439,192,1759]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figures 95–106: Barbaracurus gen. n. Figures 95–98: Barbaracurus exquisitus comb. n. Figures 95, 97. Holotype male, chelicerae, carapace and tergites I–III (95) and sternopectinal region (97). Figures 96, 98. Paratype female, chelicerae, carapace and tergites I–III (96) and sternopectinal region (98). Figures 99–106: Distal segments of right legs, retrolateral views. Figures 99–100. B. exquisitus comb. n., male holotype, legs III (99) and IV (100). Figures 101–102. B. winklerorum sp. n., male holotype, legs III (101) and IV (102). Figures 103–106. B. yemenensis sp. n., female holotype, legs I–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 99–106</figureCitation>
). Moreover, it was found that the 
<typeStatus box="[359,415,904,927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1936" box="[460,666,904,927]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis box="[460,666,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Lychas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burdoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Lychas burdoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are precisely matched in the following key characters: trichobothrial pattern, pedipalp finger dentation (
<figureCitation box="[274,410,996,1019]" captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 44–45</figureCitation>
), pectinal tooth count and pectine lamellar structure, body and appendage proportions, setation, carination and sculpture of pedipalps, carapace, tergites, sternites, form of metasoma and telson (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 40–49" captionStartId="7.[192,278,1544,1568]" captionTargetBox="[213,1411,207,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[192,1437,192,1516]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 40–49: Lychas burdoi (Simon, 1882) Figures 40, 42, 44, 48. Male paralectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (40) and ventral (42) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (44), metasoma IV–V and telson lateral (48). Figures 41, 43, 45–47, 49. Female lectotype of Babycurus ornatus Werner, 1936, dorsal (41) and ventral (43) views, pedipalp chela dorsal (45), Distal segments of right legs III (46) and IV (47) retrolateral views, and metasoma IV and telson lateral (49). Scale bar: 10 mm (40–43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figs. 40–49</figureCitation>
), as well as armature of chelicerae and pedipalp fingers. The inevitable conclusion is that 
<taxonomicName authority="Werner, 1936" authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1936" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Babycurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Babycurus ornatus</emphasis>
Werner, 1936
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Lychas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burdoi" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Lychas burdoi</emphasis>
(Simon, 1882)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[431,504,1210,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[431,470,1210,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[483,498,1210,1234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
